  "texts": [
    "17 There is no general presumption about the direction of errors in customers' risk assessment.",
    "Systematic mistakes in their risk assessment can be either positive or negative, depending on the circumstances in which a product is used, or a service is performed (Shavell, 2004, 217).",
    "Errors may also depend on the type of customer.",
    "Producers can be held liable under a strict liability standard or a negligence rule.",
    "A strict liability rule holds producers responsible for any harm caused by their products, regardless of fault."
  ],
